'''Alcoy''' is a 5th class [[Philippine municipality|municipality]] in the [[Philippine province|province]] of [[Cebu province|Cebu]], [[Philippines]]. According to the [[2000]] census, it has a population of 13,497 people in 2,435 households. It is approximately 93 kilometers from the provincial capital [[Cebu City]]. It is bounded by the municipalities of [[Dalaguete, Cebu|Dalaguete]] to the north, [[Boljoon, Cebu|Boljoon]] to the south, [[Badian, Cebu|Badian]] and [[Alegria, Cebu|Alegria]] to the west, and [[Cebu Strait]] to the east.


